ces. Presented in chronological order, each essay illuminates an aspect of combined operations during a time of changing technology and doctrine. The essays cover the war along the “rebel coast,” including the operations in the North Carolina Sounds in 1861, the Union thrusts up the York and James rivers during the Peninsular Campaign in 1862 and 1864, and the various Union efforts to seize rebel seaports from the Texas coast to Charleston and Wilmington in 1863–65. Concluding the volume are two essays that evaluate the impact of Union combined operations on subsequent doctrine in both the United States and England.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aHISTORY / Military / United States.2bisacsh1 aDuCoin, Francis J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, John P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFonvielle, Chris E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuller, Howard J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLong, David E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSheridan, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkaggs, David C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSnell, Mark A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSymonds, Craig L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSymonds, Craig L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWiser, Edward H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082323286440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329349040uhttps://www